info.title: Online Check Writer API V3
info.description:
The Onlinecheckwriter API is organized around REST. Our Api is very easy to integrate with. ## Here to Look For Help ##### **Video Help :** [Click here to watch API integration video](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kI3j_dA973Q&t=7s&utm_source=api+documenation&utm_medium=documenation&utm_campaign=api-vide&utm_id=API) For Immediate help Message Us via skype. Skype : ***onlinecheckwriter (Mon-Fri 9am5pm CST)*** Our API integration should not take more than 1 hour. If you need help [**Click here to join live chat**](https://onlinecheckwriter.com/contact/) . We can arrange zoom meeting/google meeting based on your requirement. ### Here are the step by step instructions : 1. Register/Login to [Sandbox](https://test.onlinecheckwriter.com)/[Live](https://app.onlinecheckwriter.com) 2. Get your api_token key from left bar under the Developer Panel tab 3. Now follow our api documentation. You will need to pass this api_token each time. When you are ready to go live please email [support@onlinecheckwriter.com](mailto:support@onlinecheckwriter.com) or if you have any question give message to our developer skype id : onlinecheckwriter **Api endpoint**
EnvironmentBase url
Sandboxhttps://test.onlinecheckwriter.com/api/v3
Livehttps://app.onlinecheckwriter.com/api/v3
**HTTP Methods**
MethodDescription
GETRetrieving resources
POSTCreating resources/Perform actions
PUTUpdating resources
DELETEDeleting resources
**HTTP Status Codes**
MethodDescription
200Success
201Created
400Bad request
401Unauthorized
403Forbidden
404URL /Resource Not Found
405Method Not Allowed
422Unprocessable entity
429Too many requests
500Server error
**Success Response**
AttributesDescription
successAlways true for successful response
messageSuccess messages for any resource operations
dataRequested resources
**Failure Response**
AttributesDescription
successAlways false for failure response
errorMsgHuman-readable error message

tags.name: Check
tags.description:
The API provides endpoints for creating multiple checks, retrieving individual checks, deleting checks, printing checks,updating checks and retrieving a list of checks. Check status and description
Status code Short description Full description
0 New New
1 Printed Printed
2 Void Voided
3 Arc Achieved
4 Printing Check Mailing - Printing
5 Printed Check Mailing - Printed Your Check
6 Printed Check Mailing - Printed Envelop
7 Mailed Check Mailing - Mailed
8 Printed Check Mailing - Mailed(Reservered For Manual Action)
11 Refunded Check Mailing - Refunded (Please call our customer support & resolve the issue)
12 E-Mailed E-Mailed
13 E-Mailed E-Mailed
14 E-Printed E-Printed
50 Schedule Schedule For Future Mailing
300 DD Direct Deposit
301 DD Direct Deposit is not deposited from receiver
302 DD Direct Deposit Initiated
303 DD Direct Deposit Processing
304 DDC Direct Deposit Completed
305 DD/F Direct Deposit Failed
306 DD/V Direct Deposit Voided
308 Pushing Processing on Pushing
311 DD/R Return From Provider
312 DD/R Reject from Operator. Please call our customer support team for further query
313 DD/AR Application Rejected

tags.name: ACH
tags.description:
Ach Payment. Ach Payment may not work unless we manually approve your account. Please talk to our technical support team to enable it for you. ACH STATUS
Status Description Meaning
400 DD Direct Deposit Initiated
410 DD-FUNDING Funding started
411 DD Funding completed
412 DD Failed DD Funding Failed PF
420 DDC DD Completed/Credited receiver wallet
430 DD-DEPOSITING Depositing started
431 DDC Direct deposit completed
432 DD-DEPOSIT-F Direct deposit failed
433 DD-BA-NOT-VERIFIED Bank account verification required for depositing
440 DD/F Direct Deposit Failed

post.description:
You can create multiple checks in one single request by passing check attributes. If you would like to create check with advance stub you need to pass voucherId or voucher data as follow sample request. Payload parameters
checks Required Array

An array of check attributes
check attributes
bankAccountId Required String

Must be a bank account ID
payeeId Required String

Must be a payee ID Optional if noPayee is true, otherwise required.

categoryId Optional String

Must be a category ID
serialNumber Optional String

By default increment every time a check is created, If a serialNumber is passed, that will override any default.
issueDate Optional String yyyy-mm-dd

By default it will be check creation date, If a issueDate is passed, that will override any default.
amount Required Decimal

Optional if noAmount is true, otherwise required.
memo Optional String

Max of 150 characters to be included on the memo line of the check.
note Optional String

An internal note that identifies this check. Must be no longer than 150 characters.

accountNumber Optional String

Any account number associated with this check
invoiceNumber Optional String

Any invoice number associated with this check
noSign Optional Boolean

if true ,check will create without signature ,By default false

noAmount Optional Boolean

iftrue ,check will create without amount,By default false

noDate Optional Boolean

if true ,check will create without date,By default false

noPayee Optional Boolean

if true ,check will create without payee,By default false

voucherId Optional String

Must be an voucher ID, It will be ignored if object of voucher attributes passed.
voucher Optional Object

Must be an object of voucher attributes

This API allows you to upload PDF file as attachment, There are two types of uploads you can perform: Upload via remote URL with, (fileUrl) You can provide any remote public accessible url as ’fileUrl’ parameter , this file will be fetched and will be added as attachment Simple Upload (attachment), You can directly upload the file via post method Path parameters

Id of the Check.

Must be a public accessible url ,Optional if attachment is passed
